59static unsigned char auth_hmd5[] = {
60 0x05, 0x5f, 0x61, 0x75, 0x74, 0x68, /*%< len + _auth */
61 ISCCC_CCMSGTYPE_TABLE, /*%< message type */
62 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x20, /*%< length == 32 */
63 0x04, 0x68, 0x6d, 0x64, 0x35, /*%< len + hmd5 */
64 ISCCC_CCMSGTYPE_BINARYDATA, /*%< message type */
65 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x16, /*%< length == 22 */
66 /*
67 * The base64 encoding of one of our HMAC-MD5 signatures is
68 * 22 bytes.
69 */
70 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
71 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
72 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00
73};
74
75#define HMD5_OFFSET 21 /*%< 21 = 6 + 1 + 4 + 5 + 1 + 4 */
76#define HMD5_LENGTH 22
77
78static unsigned char auth_hsha[] = {
79 0x05, 0x5f, 0x61, 0x75, 0x74, 0x68, /*%< len + _auth */
80 ISCCC_CCMSGTYPE_TABLE, /*%< message type */
81 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x63, /*%< length == 99 */
82 0x04, 0x68, 0x73, 0x68, 0x61, /*%< len + hsha */
83 ISCCC_CCMSGTYPE_BINARYDATA, /*%< message type */
84 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x59, /*%< length == 89 */
85 0x00, /*%< algorithm */
86 /*
87 * The base64 encoding of one of our HMAC-SHA* signatures is
88 * 88 bytes.
89 */
90 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
91 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
92 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
93 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
94 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
95 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
96 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
97 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
98 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
99 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
100 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00
101};

103#define HSHA_OFFSET 22 /*%< 21 = 6 + 1 + 4 + 5 + 1 + 4 + 1 */
104#define HSHA_LENGTH 88

106static isc_result_t
107table_towire(isccc_sexpr_t *alist, isc_buffer_t **buffer);
108
109static isc_result_t
110list_towire(isccc_sexpr_t *alist, isc_buffer_t **buffer);
111
112static isc_result_t
113value_towire(isccc_sexpr_t *elt, isc_buffer_t **buffer) {
114 unsigned int len;
115 isccc_region_t *vr;
116 isc_result_t result;
117
118 if (isccc_sexpr_binaryp(elt)) {
119 vr = isccc_sexpr_tobinary(elt);
120 len = REGION_SIZE(*vr);
121 result = isc_buffer_reserve(buffer, 1 + 4);
122 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
123 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
124 isc_buffer_putuint8(*buffer, ISCCC_CCMSGTYPE_BINARYDATA);
125 isc_buffer_putuint32(*buffer, len);
126
127 result = isc_buffer_reserve(buffer, len);
128 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
129 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
130 isc_buffer_putmem(*buffer, vr->rstart, len);
131 } else if (isccc_alist_alistp(elt)) {
132 unsigned int used;
133 isc_buffer_t b;
134
135 result = isc_buffer_reserve(buffer, 1 + 4);
136 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
137 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
138 isc_buffer_putuint8(*buffer, ISCCC_CCMSGTYPE_TABLE);
139 /*
140 * Emit a placeholder length.
141 */
142 used = (*buffer)->used;
143 isc_buffer_putuint32(*buffer, 0);
144
145 /*
146 * Emit the table.
147 */
148 result = table_towire(elt, buffer);
149 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
150 return (result);
151
152 len = (*buffer)->used - used;
153 /*
154 * 'len' is 4 bytes too big, since it counts
155 * the placeholder length too. Adjust and
156 * emit.
157 */
158 INSIST(len >= 4U);
159 len -= 4;
160
161 isc_buffer_init(&b, (unsigned char *) (*buffer)->base + used, 4);
162 isc_buffer_putuint32(&b, len);
163 } else if (isccc_sexpr_listp(elt)) {
164 unsigned int used;
165 isc_buffer_t b;
166
167 result = isc_buffer_reserve(buffer, 1 + 4);
168 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
169 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
170 isc_buffer_putuint8(*buffer, ISCCC_CCMSGTYPE_LIST);
171 /*
172 * Emit a placeholder length.
173 */
174 used = (*buffer)->used;
175 isc_buffer_putuint32(*buffer, 0);
176
177 /*
178 * Emit the list.
179 */
180 result = list_towire(elt, buffer);
181 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
182 return (result);
183
184 len = (*buffer)->used - used;
185 /*
186 * 'len' is 4 bytes too big, since it counts
187 * the placeholder length too. Adjust and
188 * emit.
189 */
190 INSIST(len >= 4U);
191 len -= 4;
192
193 isc_buffer_init(&b, (unsigned char *) (*buffer)->base + used, 4);
194 isc_buffer_putuint32(&b, len);
195 }
196
197 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
198}
199
200static isc_result_t
201table_towire(isccc_sexpr_t *alist, isc_buffer_t **buffer) {
202 isccc_sexpr_t *kv, *elt, *k, *v;
203 char *ks;
204 isc_result_t result;
205 unsigned int len;
206
207 for (elt = isccc_alist_first(alist);
208 elt != NULL;
209 elt = ISCCC_SEXPR_CDR(elt)) {
210 kv = ISCCC_SEXPR_CAR(elt);
211 k = ISCCC_SEXPR_CAR(kv);
212 ks = isccc_sexpr_tostring(k);
213 v = ISCCC_SEXPR_CDR(kv);
214 len = (unsigned int)strlen(ks);
215 INSIST(len <= 255U);
216 /*
217 * Emit the key name.
218 */
219 result = isc_buffer_reserve(buffer, 1 + len);
220 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
221 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
222 isc_buffer_putuint8(*buffer, (uint8_t)len);
223 isc_buffer_putmem(*buffer, (const unsigned char *) ks, len);
224 /*
225 * Emit the value.
226 */
227 result = value_towire(v, buffer);
228 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
229 return (result);
230 }
231
232 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
233}
234
235static isc_result_t
236list_towire(isccc_sexpr_t *list, isc_buffer_t **buffer) {
237 isc_result_t result;
238
239 while (list != NULL) {
240 result = value_towire(ISCCC_SEXPR_CAR(list), buffer);
241 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
242 return (result);
243 list = ISCCC_SEXPR_CDR(list);
244 }
245
246 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
247}
248
249static isc_result_t
250sign(unsigned char *data, unsigned int length, unsigned char *hmac,
251 uint32_t algorithm, isccc_region_t *secret)
252{
253 isc_md_type_t md_type;
254 isc_result_t result;
255 isccc_region_t source, target;
256 unsigned char digest[ISC_MAX_MD_SIZE];
257 unsigned int digestlen;
258 unsigned char digestb64[HSHA_LENGTH + 4];
259
260 source.rstart = digest;
261
262 switch (algorithm) {
263 case ISCCC_ALG_HMACMD5:
264 md_type = ISC_MD_MD5;
265 break;
266 case ISCCC_ALG_HMACSHA1:
267 md_type = ISC_MD_SHA1;
268 break;
269 case ISCCC_ALG_HMACSHA224:
270 md_type = ISC_MD_SHA224;
271 break;
272 case ISCCC_ALG_HMACSHA256:
273 md_type = ISC_MD_SHA256;
274 break;
275 case ISCCC_ALG_HMACSHA384:
276 md_type = ISC_MD_SHA384;
277 break;
278 case ISCCC_ALG_HMACSHA512:
279 md_type = ISC_MD_SHA512;
280 break;
281 default:
282 return (ISC_R_NOTIMPLEMENTED);
283 }
284
285 result = isc_hmac(md_type,
286 secret->rstart, REGION_SIZE(*secret),
287 data, length,
288 digest, &digestlen);
289 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
290 return (result);
291 }
292 source.rend = digest + digestlen;
293
294 memset(digestb64, 0, sizeof(digestb64));
295 target.rstart = digestb64;
296 target.rend = digestb64 + sizeof(digestb64);
297 result = isccc_base64_encode(&source, 64, "", &target);
298 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
299 return (result);
300 if (algorithm == ISCCC_ALG_HMACMD5)
301 PUT_MEM(digestb64, HMD5_LENGTH, hmac);
302 else
303 PUT_MEM(digestb64, HSHA_LENGTH, hmac);
304 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
305}
306
307isc_result_t
308isccc_cc_towire(isccc_sexpr_t *alist, isc_buffer_t **buffer,
309 uint32_t algorithm, isccc_region_t *secret)
310{
311 unsigned int hmac_base, signed_base;
312 isc_result_t result;
313
314 result = isc_buffer_reserve(buffer,
315 4 + ((algorithm == ISCCC_ALG_HMACMD5) ?
316 sizeof(auth_hmd5) :
317 sizeof(auth_hsha)));
318 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
319 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
320
321 /*
322 * Emit protocol version.
323 */
324 isc_buffer_putuint32(*buffer, 1);
325
326 if (secret != NULL) {
327 /*
328 * Emit _auth section with zeroed HMAC signature.
329 * We'll replace the zeros with the real signature once
330 * we know what it is.
331 */
332 if (algorithm == ISCCC_ALG_HMACMD5) {
333 hmac_base = (*buffer)->used + HMD5_OFFSET;
334 isc_buffer_putmem(*buffer,
335 auth_hmd5, sizeof(auth_hmd5));
336 } else
337 {
338 unsigned char *hmac_alg;
339
340 hmac_base = (*buffer)->used + HSHA_OFFSET;
341 hmac_alg = (unsigned char *) isc_buffer_used(*buffer) +
342 HSHA_OFFSET - 1;
343 isc_buffer_putmem(*buffer,
344 auth_hsha, sizeof(auth_hsha));
345 *hmac_alg = algorithm;
346 }
347 } else
348 hmac_base = 0;
349 signed_base = (*buffer)->used;
350 /*
351 * Delete any existing _auth section so that we don't try
352 * to encode it.
353 */
354 isccc_alist_delete(alist, "_auth");
355 /*
356 * Emit the message.
357 */
358 result = table_towire(alist, buffer);
359 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
360 return (result);
361 if (secret != NULL)
362 return (sign((unsigned char *) (*buffer)->base + signed_base,
363 (*buffer)->used - signed_base,
364 (unsigned char *) (*buffer)->base + hmac_base,
365 algorithm, secret));
366 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
367}

369static isc_result_t
370verify(isccc_sexpr_t *alist, unsigned char *data, unsigned int length,
371 uint32_t algorithm, isccc_region_t *secret)
372{
373 isc_md_type_t md_type;
374 isccc_region_t source;
375 isccc_region_t target;
376 isc_result_t result;
377 isccc_sexpr_t *_auth, *hmac;
378 unsigned char digest[ISC_MAX_MD_SIZE];
379 unsigned int digestlen;
380 unsigned char digestb64[HSHA_LENGTH * 4];
381
382 /*
383 * Extract digest.
384 */
385 _auth = isccc_alist_lookup(alist, "_auth");
386 if (!isccc_alist_alistp(_auth))
387 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
388 if (algorithm == ISCCC_ALG_HMACMD5)
389 hmac = isccc_alist_lookup(_auth, "hmd5");
390 else
391 hmac = isccc_alist_lookup(_auth, "hsha");
392 if (!isccc_sexpr_binaryp(hmac))
393 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
394 /*
395 * Compute digest.
396 */
397 source.rstart = digest;
398
399 switch (algorithm) {
400 case ISCCC_ALG_HMACMD5:
401 md_type = ISC_MD_MD5;
402 break;
403 case ISCCC_ALG_HMACSHA1:
404 md_type = ISC_MD_SHA1;
405 break;
406 case ISCCC_ALG_HMACSHA224:
407 md_type = ISC_MD_SHA224;
408 break;
409 case ISCCC_ALG_HMACSHA256:
410 md_type = ISC_MD_SHA256;
411 break;
412 case ISCCC_ALG_HMACSHA384:
413 md_type = ISC_MD_SHA384;
414 break;
415 case ISCCC_ALG_HMACSHA512:
416 md_type = ISC_MD_SHA512;
417 break;
418 default:
419 return (ISC_R_NOTIMPLEMENTED);
420 }
421
422 result = isc_hmac(md_type,
423 secret->rstart, REGION_SIZE(*secret),
424 data, length,
425 digest, &digestlen);
426 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
427 return (result);
428 }
429 source.rend = digest + digestlen;
430
431 target.rstart = digestb64;
432 target.rend = digestb64 + sizeof(digestb64);
433 memset(digestb64, 0, sizeof(digestb64));
434 result = isccc_base64_encode(&source, 64, "", &target);
435 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
436 return (result);
437
438 /*
439 * Verify.
440 */
441 if (algorithm == ISCCC_ALG_HMACMD5) {
442 isccc_region_t *region;
443 unsigned char *value;
444
445 region = isccc_sexpr_tobinary(hmac);
446 if ((region->rend - region->rstart) != HMD5_LENGTH)
447 return (ISCCC_R_BADAUTH);
448 value = region->rstart;
449 if (!isc_safe_memequal(value, digestb64, HMD5_LENGTH))
450 return (ISCCC_R_BADAUTH);
451 } else {
452 isccc_region_t *region;
453 unsigned char *value;
454 uint32_t valalg;
455
456 region = isccc_sexpr_tobinary(hmac);
457
458 /*
459 * Note: with non-MD5 algorithms, there's an extra octet
460 * to identify which algorithm is in use.
461 */
462 if ((region->rend - region->rstart) != HSHA_LENGTH + 1)
463 return (ISCCC_R_BADAUTH);
464 value = region->rstart;
465 GET8(valalg, value);
466 if ((valalg != algorithm) ||
467 !isc_safe_memequal(value, digestb64, HSHA_LENGTH))
468 return (ISCCC_R_BADAUTH);
469 }
470
471 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
472}

474static isc_result_t
475table_fromwire(isccc_region_t *source, isccc_region_t *secret,
476 uint32_t algorithm, isccc_sexpr_t **alistp);
477
478static isc_result_t
479list_fromwire(isccc_region_t *source, isccc_sexpr_t **listp);
480
481static isc_result_t
482value_fromwire(isccc_region_t *source, isccc_sexpr_t **valuep) {
483 unsigned int msgtype;
484 uint32_t len;
485 isccc_sexpr_t *value;
486 isccc_region_t active;
487 isc_result_t result;
488
489 if (REGION_SIZE(*source) < 1 + 4)
490 return (ISC_R_UNEXPECTEDEND);
491 GET8(msgtype, source->rstart);
492 GET32(len, source->rstart);
493 if (REGION_SIZE(*source) < len)
494 return (ISC_R_UNEXPECTEDEND);
495 active.rstart = source->rstart;
496 active.rend = active.rstart + len;
497 source->rstart = active.rend;
498 if (msgtype == ISCCC_CCMSGTYPE_BINARYDATA) {
499 value = isccc_sexpr_frombinary(&active);
500 if (value != NULL) {
501 *valuep = value;
502 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
503 } else
504 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
505 } else if (msgtype == ISCCC_CCMSGTYPE_TABLE)
506 result = table_fromwire(&active, NULL, 0, valuep);
507 else if (msgtype == ISCCC_CCMSGTYPE_LIST)
508 result = list_fromwire(&active, valuep);
509 else
510 result = ISCCC_R_SYNTAX;
511
512 return (result);
513}
514
515static isc_result_t
516table_fromwire(isccc_region_t *source, isccc_region_t *secret,
517 uint32_t algorithm, isccc_sexpr_t **alistp)
518{
519 char key[256];
520 uint32_t len;
521 isc_result_t result;
522 isccc_sexpr_t *alist, *value;
523 bool first_tag;
524 unsigned char *checksum_rstart;
525
526 REQUIRE(alistp != NULL && *alistp == NULL);
527
528 checksum_rstart = NULL;
529 first_tag = true;
530 alist = isccc_alist_create();
531 if (alist == NULL)
532 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
533
534 while (!REGION_EMPTY(*source)) {
535 GET8(len, source->rstart);
536 if (REGION_SIZE(*source) < len) {
537 result = ISC_R_UNEXPECTEDEND;
538 goto bad;
539 }
540 GET_MEM(key, len, source->rstart);
541 key[len] = '\0'; /* Ensure NUL termination. */
542 value = NULL;
543 result = value_fromwire(source, &value);
544 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
545 goto bad;
546 if (isccc_alist_define(alist, key, value) == NULL) {
547 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
548 goto bad;
549 }
550 if (first_tag && secret != NULL && strcmp(key, "_auth") == 0)
551 checksum_rstart = source->rstart;
552 first_tag = false;
553 }
554
555 if (secret != NULL) {
556 if (checksum_rstart != NULL)
557 result = verify(alist, checksum_rstart,
558 (unsigned int)
559 (source->rend - checksum_rstart),
560 algorithm, secret);
561 else
562 result = ISCCC_R_BADAUTH;
563 } else
564 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
565
566 bad:
567 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
568 *alistp = alist;
569 else
570 isccc_sexpr_free(&alist);
571
572 return (result);
573}
574
575static isc_result_t
576list_fromwire(isccc_region_t *source, isccc_sexpr_t **listp) {
577 isccc_sexpr_t *list, *value;
578 isc_result_t result;
579
580 list = NULL;
581 while (!REGION_EMPTY(*source)) {
582 value = NULL;
583 result = value_fromwire(source, &value);
584 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
585 isccc_sexpr_free(&list);
586 return (result);
587 }
588 if (isccc_sexpr_addtolist(&list, value) == NULL) {
589 isccc_sexpr_free(&value);
590 isccc_sexpr_free(&list);
591 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
592 }
593 }
594
595 *listp = list;
596
597 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
598}
599
600isc_result_t
601isccc_cc_fromwire(isccc_region_t *source, isccc_sexpr_t **alistp,
602 uint32_t algorithm, isccc_region_t *secret)
603{
604 unsigned int size;
605 uint32_t version;
606
607 size = REGION_SIZE(*source);
608 if (size < 4)
609 return (ISC_R_UNEXPECTEDEND);
610 GET32(version, source->rstart);
611 if (version != 1)
612 return (ISCCC_R_UNKNOWNVERSION);
613
614 return (table_fromwire(source, secret, algorithm, alistp));
615}
616
617static isc_result_t
618createmessage(uint32_t version, const char *from, const char *to,
619 uint32_t serial, isccc_time_t now,
620 isccc_time_t expires, isccc_sexpr_t **alistp,
621 bool want_expires)
622{
623 isccc_sexpr_t *alist, *_ctrl, *_data;
624 isc_result_t result;
625
626 REQUIRE(alistp != NULL && *alistp == NULL);
627
628 if (version != 1)
629 return (ISCCC_R_UNKNOWNVERSION);
630
631 alist = isccc_alist_create();
632 if (alist == NULL)
633 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
634
635 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
636
637 _ctrl = isccc_alist_create();
638 if (_ctrl == NULL)
639 goto bad;
640 if (isccc_alist_define(alist, "_ctrl", _ctrl) == NULL) {
641 isccc_sexpr_free(&_ctrl);
642 goto bad;
643 }
644
645 _data = isccc_alist_create();
646 if (_data == NULL)
647 goto bad;
648 if (isccc_alist_define(alist, "_data", _data) == NULL) {
649 isccc_sexpr_free(&_data);
650 goto bad;
651 }
652
653 if (isccc_cc_defineuint32(_ctrl, "_ser", serial) == NULL ||
654 isccc_cc_defineuint32(_ctrl, "_tim", now) == NULL ||
655 (want_expires &&
656 isccc_cc_defineuint32(_ctrl, "_exp", expires) == NULL))
657 goto bad;
658 if (from != NULL &&
659 isccc_cc_definestring(_ctrl, "_frm", from) == NULL)
660 goto bad;
661 if (to != NULL &&
662 isccc_cc_definestring(_ctrl, "_to", to) == NULL)
663 goto bad;
664
665 *alistp = alist;
666
667 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
668
669 bad:
670 isccc_sexpr_free(&alist);
671
672 return (result);
673}
674
675isc_result_t
676isccc_cc_createmessage(uint32_t version, const char *from, const char *to,
677 uint32_t serial, isccc_time_t now,
678 isccc_time_t expires, isccc_sexpr_t **alistp)
679{
680 return (createmessage(version, from, to, serial, now, expires,
681 alistp, true));
682}
683
684isc_result_t
685isccc_cc_createack(isccc_sexpr_t *message, bool ok,
686 isccc_sexpr_t **ackp)
687{
688 char *_frm, *_to;
689 uint32_t serial;
690 isccc_sexpr_t *ack, *_ctrl;
691 isc_result_t result;
692 isccc_time_t t;
693
694 REQUIRE(ackp != NULL && *ackp == NULL);
695
696 _ctrl = isccc_alist_lookup(message, "_ctrl");
697 if (!isccc_alist_alistp(_ctrl) ||
698 isccc_cc_lookupuint32(_ctrl, "_ser", &serial) != ISC_R_SUCCESS ||
699 isccc_cc_lookupuint32(_ctrl, "_tim", &t) != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
700 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
701 /*
702 * _frm and _to are optional.
703 */
704 _frm = NULL;
705 (void)isccc_cc_lookupstring(_ctrl, "_frm", &_frm);
706 _to = NULL;
707 (void)isccc_cc_lookupstring(_ctrl, "_to", &_to);
708 /*
709 * Create the ack.
710 */
711 ack = NULL;
712 result = createmessage(1, _to, _frm, serial, t, 0, &ack, false);
713 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
714 return (result);
715
716 _ctrl = isccc_alist_lookup(ack, "_ctrl");
717 if (_ctrl == NULL) {
718 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
719 goto bad;
720 }
721 if (isccc_cc_definestring(ack, "_ack", (ok) ? "1" : "0") == NULL) {
722 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
723 goto bad;
724 }
725
726 *ackp = ack;
727
728 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
729
730 bad:
731 isccc_sexpr_free(&ack);
732
733 return (result);
734}
735
736bool
737isccc_cc_isack(isccc_sexpr_t *message) {
738 isccc_sexpr_t *_ctrl;
739
740 _ctrl = isccc_alist_lookup(message, "_ctrl");
741 if (!isccc_alist_alistp(_ctrl))
742 return (false);
743 if (isccc_cc_lookupstring(_ctrl, "_ack", NULL) == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
744 return (true);
745 return (false);
746}
747
748bool
749isccc_cc_isreply(isccc_sexpr_t *message) {
750 isccc_sexpr_t *_ctrl;
751
752 _ctrl = isccc_alist_lookup(message, "_ctrl");
753 if (!isccc_alist_alistp(_ctrl))
754 return (false);
755 if (isccc_cc_lookupstring(_ctrl, "_rpl", NULL) == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
756 return (true);
757 return (false);
758}
759
760isc_result_t
761isccc_cc_createresponse(isccc_sexpr_t *message, isccc_time_t now,
762 isccc_time_t expires, isccc_sexpr_t **alistp)
763{
764 char *_frm, *_to, *type = NULL;
765 uint32_t serial;
766 isccc_sexpr_t *alist, *_ctrl, *_data;
767 isc_result_t result;
768
769 REQUIRE(alistp != NULL && *alistp == NULL);
770
771 _ctrl = isccc_alist_lookup(message, "_ctrl");
772 _data = isccc_alist_lookup(message, "_data");
773 if (!isccc_alist_alistp(_ctrl) || !isccc_alist_alistp(_data) ||
774 isccc_cc_lookupuint32(_ctrl, "_ser", &serial) != ISC_R_SUCCESS ||
775 isccc_cc_lookupstring(_data, "type", &type) != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
776 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
777 /*
778 * _frm and _to are optional.
779 */
780 _frm = NULL;
781 (void)isccc_cc_lookupstring(_ctrl, "_frm", &_frm);
782 _to = NULL;
783 (void)isccc_cc_lookupstring(_ctrl, "_to", &_to);
784 /*
785 * Create the response.
786 */
787 alist = NULL;
788 result = isccc_cc_createmessage(1, _to, _frm, serial, now, expires,
789 &alist);
790 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
791 return (result);
792
793 _ctrl = isccc_alist_lookup(alist, "_ctrl");
794 if (_ctrl == NULL) {
795 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
796 goto bad;
797 }
798
799 _data = isccc_alist_lookup(alist, "_data");
800 if (_data == NULL) {
801 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
802 goto bad;
803 }
804
805 if (isccc_cc_definestring(_ctrl, "_rpl", "1") == NULL ||
806 isccc_cc_definestring(_data, "type", type) == NULL)
807 {
808 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
809 goto bad;
810 }
811
812 *alistp = alist;
813
814 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
815
816 bad:
817 isccc_sexpr_free(&alist);
818 return (result);
819}
820
821isccc_sexpr_t *
822isccc_cc_definestring(isccc_sexpr_t *alist, const char *key, const char *str) {
823 size_t len;
824 isccc_region_t r;
825
826 len = strlen(str);
827 DE_CONST(str, r.rstart);
828 r.rend = r.rstart + len;
829
830 return (isccc_alist_definebinary(alist, key, &r));
831}
832
833isccc_sexpr_t *
834isccc_cc_defineuint32(isccc_sexpr_t *alist, const char *key, uint32_t i) {
835 char b[100];
836 size_t len;
837 isccc_region_t r;
838
839 snprintf(b, sizeof(b), "%u", i);
840 len = strlen(b);
841 r.rstart = (unsigned char *)b;
842 r.rend = (unsigned char *)b + len;
843
844 return (isccc_alist_definebinary(alist, key, &r));
845}
846
847isc_result_t
848isccc_cc_lookupstring(isccc_sexpr_t *alist, const char *key, char **strp) {
849 isccc_sexpr_t *kv, *v;
850
851 REQUIRE(strp == NULL || *strp == NULL);
852
853 kv = isccc_alist_assq(alist, key);
854 if (kv != NULL) {
855 v = ISCCC_SEXPR_CDR(kv);
856 if (isccc_sexpr_binaryp(v)) {
857 if (strp != NULL)
858 *strp = isccc_sexpr_tostring(v);
859 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
860 } else
861 return (ISC_R_EXISTS);
862 }
863
864 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
865}
866
867isc_result_t
868isccc_cc_lookupuint32(isccc_sexpr_t *alist, const char *key,
869 uint32_t *uintp)
870{
871 isccc_sexpr_t *kv, *v;
872
873 kv = isccc_alist_assq(alist, key);
874 if (kv != NULL) {
875 v = ISCCC_SEXPR_CDR(kv);
876 if (isccc_sexpr_binaryp(v)) {
877 if (uintp != NULL)
878 *uintp = (uint32_t)
879 strtoul(isccc_sexpr_tostring(v),
880 NULL, 10);
881 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
882 } else
883 return (ISC_R_EXISTS);
884 }
885
886 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
887}

889static void
890symtab_undefine(char *key, unsigned int type, isccc_symvalue_t value,
891 void *arg)
892{
893 UNUSED(type);
894 UNUSED(value);
895 UNUSED(arg);
896
897 free(key);
898}

900static bool
901symtab_clean(char *key, unsigned int type, isccc_symvalue_t value, void *arg) {
902 isccc_time_t *now;
903
904 UNUSED(key);
905 UNUSED(type);
906
907 now = arg;
908
909 if (*now < value.as_uinteger)
910 return (false);
911 if ((*now - value.as_uinteger) < DUP_LIFETIME)
912 return (false);
913 return (true);
914}

916isc_result_t
917isccc_cc_createsymtab(isccc_symtab_t **symtabp) {
918 return (isccc_symtab_create(11897, symtab_undefine, NULL, false,
919 symtabp));
920}

922void
923isccc_cc_cleansymtab(isccc_symtab_t *symtab, isccc_time_t now) {
924 isccc_symtab_foreach(symtab, symtab_clean, &now);
925}
926
927static bool
928has_whitespace(const char *str) {
929 char c;
930
931 if (str == NULL)
932 return (false);
933 while ((c = *str++) != '\0') {
934 if (c == ' ' || c == '\t' || c == '\n')
935 return (true);
936 }
937 return (false);
938}
939
940isc_result_t
941isccc_cc_checkdup(isccc_symtab_t *symtab, isccc_sexpr_t *message,
942 isccc_time_t now)
943{
944 const char *_frm;
945 const char *_to;
946 char *_ser = NULL, *_tim = NULL, *tmp;
947 isc_result_t result;
948 char *key;
949 size_t len;
950 isccc_symvalue_t value;
951 isccc_sexpr_t *_ctrl;
952
953 _ctrl = isccc_alist_lookup(message, "_ctrl");
954 if (!isccc_alist_alistp(_ctrl) ||
955 isccc_cc_lookupstring(_ctrl, "_ser", &_ser) != ISC_R_SUCCESS ||
956 isccc_cc_lookupstring(_ctrl, "_tim", &_tim) != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
957 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
958
959 INSIST(_ser != NULL);
960 INSIST(_tim != NULL);
961
962 /*
963 * _frm and _to are optional.
964 */
965 tmp = NULL;
966 if (isccc_cc_lookupstring(_ctrl, "_frm", &tmp) != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
967 _frm = "";
968 else
969 _frm = tmp;
970 tmp = NULL;
971 if (isccc_cc_lookupstring(_ctrl, "_to", &tmp) != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
972 _to = "";
973 else
974 _to = tmp;
975 /*
976 * Ensure there is no newline in any of the strings. This is so
977 * we can write them to a file later.
978 */
979 if (has_whitespace(_frm) || has_whitespace(_to) ||
980 has_whitespace(_ser) || has_whitespace(_tim))
981 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
982 len = strlen(_frm) + strlen(_to) + strlen(_ser) + strlen(_tim) + 4;
983 key = malloc(len);
984 if (key == NULL)
985 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
986 snprintf(key, len, "%s;%s;%s;%s", _frm, _to, _ser, _tim);
987 value.as_uinteger = now;
988 result = isccc_symtab_define(symtab, key, ISCCC_SYMTYPE_CCDUP, value,
989 isccc_symexists_reject);
990 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
991 free(key);
992 return (result);
993 }
994
995 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
996}
